Change Log for SQLCMD Program
=============================

@(#)$Id: ChangeLog,v 2016.1 2016/07/28 19:53:09 jleffler Exp $

Version 90.02
-------------
2016-07-28: Version 90.02 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2016-07-28: Generate error message instead of assertion failure if argument
            to -D, -E, -G, -Q is (massively) too long.  Issue raised by Art
            Kagel <art.kagel@gmail.com> on behalf of Adam Tauno Williams
            <awilliam@whitemiceconsulting.com> with problem probably caused
            by quote handling in myexport.sh.  The grammar files
            (connecty.y, connect.h) already limit these in LOAD, RELOAD and
            UNLOAD statements.

Version 90.01
-------------
2015-11-14: Version 90.01 - Limited release.
2015-11-14: Explicitly set IFX_DEFERRED_PREPARE=0 in environment to avoid
            problems when it is set to 1.  SQLCMD expects PREPARE to tell
            it what type of statement it is processing and gets upset if
            that information is deferred.  Problem reported by Eric Byrnes
            <eric.byrnes@bldr.com>.
2015-11-14: Arrange to suppress #pragma GCC lines that can cause problems
            with GCC 4.5.x and earlier.  They are primarily to reassure the
            maintainer that the code is clean and don't really affect end
            users (unless the default compilation options are made much
            more stringent).  Problem reported in October by Ray Burns
            <Ray.Burns@velocityglobal.co.nz>.

Version 90.00
-------------
2015-11-08: Version 90.00 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2015-07-17: Move documentation to share/man/man1 (instead of man/man1).
2015-07-16: Add support for 'block' output format (e.g. sqlcmd -F block).
            Closely based on a patch provided by Øyvind Gjerstad
            <oyvind.gjerstad@postnord.com>.  Simulates DB-Access output
            format, with each row printed with the column name on the left
            and the value on the right.

Version 89.03
-------------
2015-07-10: Version 89.03 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2015-07-10: Warn when -u or -p options appear after -d on command line.
2015-07-10: Sundry cleanup operations (posixver.h, etc).
2015-07-10: Ensure correct handling of WHERE in connblob.ec

Version 89.02
-------------
2014-07-27: Version 89.02.
2014-07-27: Report when exit status from system() is non-zero, avoiding
            compilation warning on Ubuntu 14.04.

Version 89.01
-------------
2013-12-28: Version 89.01.
2013-12-28: Fix selblob code (broken, unspotted, since May 2008; reported
            by Chris Wolf <Chris.Wolf@sungardps.com>).  Rudimentary test
            for selblob.  Option handling changes in selblob, appblob,
            selmultiblob. Fix independent build for selmultiblob.

Version 89.00
-------------
2013-09-08: Version 89.00 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2013-09-08: Fix compilation warnings under stringent compilation options,
            reported by Øyvind Gjerstad <ogj@tollpost.no>.
2013-09-08: Fix compilation warnings from GNU Readline under very stringent
            compilation options, introducing gnureadline.h to centralize
            the hackery.

Version 88.02
-------------
2012-10-28: Version 88.02 - Limited distribution.
2012-10-28: Fix serious malformatting of characters needing escapes
            (reported by Dirk Bornhütter <dirk@bornhuetter.de> via Art
            Kagel).
2012-08-14: Redo sleep command to avoid C99 interleaved declarations and
            statements.  Reported by Art Kagel <art.kagel@gmail.com> on
            behalf of a client using AIX 5.2.  It is not clear whether
            configure.ac is using AC_PROG_CC_C99 correctly.

Version 88.01
-------------
2012-08-05: Version 88.01 - Never formally released to anybody.
2012-08-05: Add omitted keywords to keyword rule in connecty.y.

Version 88.00
-------------
2012-07-20: Version 88.00 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2012-07-19: Finish support for -b (DB-Access -X).  In DB-Access, SELECT
            and OUTPUT are not affected by -X; in SQLCMD, SELECT is.
2012-06-21: Support fractional seconds in sleep.  If the system supports
            usleep() but not nanosleep() or clock_nanosleep(), then any
            sleep requested that is longer than 1000 seconds is converted
            to a plain sleep() call with no sub-second component.
2011-11-02: Add '-b' to support DB-Access hex (-X) mode input and output,
            as requested by Kernoal Stephens <kernoals@gmail.com>.
2011-09-02: Build: MacOS X Lion (10.7) needs ranlib on updated libraries.
2011-09-02: Configure for memmem() - MacOS X Lion (10.7) has it too.
2011-05-12: Improve formatting of column names and types; responds to the
            different format options.  Fixed widths should be the same for
            headings, types and data (needs major data structure changes).

Version 87.02
-------------
2010-12-18: Version 87.02 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2010-12-18: Add support for connections establishing trusted contexts.

Version 87.01
-------------
2010-12-06: Version 87.01 - Limited distribution.
2010-12-06: Dusan Simic <dusan.simic@versaterm.com> reports compiling 86.00
            and 87.00 on AIX 6.1; related to memmem() and C99; fixed.

Version 87.00
-------------
2010-10-21: Version 87.00 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2010-10-21: Fix bug found by Eric Haszlakiewicz <ehaszla@transunion.com> in
            UNLOAD with delimiter, and related bugs that are now obvious.
2010-10-13: Introduce -G eor to set EOR on command line.  Fix escaping so
            if EOR is (say) '\f', newlines in data are not escaped.  For
            multi-character EOR (such as CRLF), escape first character (CR)
            but not second (LF) or subsequent (but is that correct, or
            should all characters in EOR string be escaped?).  Also, do we
            check for overlap of EOR with delimiter and escape?  Add
            $DBNEWLINE as environment variable parallel to DBDELIMITER,
            DBESCAPE, DBQUOTE.
2010-09-25: Reinstate stderr.[ch] v8.x technology as v10.x
2010-09-25: Patch from Øyvind Gjerstad <ogj@tollpost.no> to fix bug in
            HTML output.

Version 86.09
-------------
2010-09-10: Version 86.09 - Uploaded to IIUG.
2010-09-10: People actively running into the POSIX getline() problem.
2010-05-26: Various changes in preparation for things to come (in 87.xx).

Version 86.08
-------------
2010-05-16: Version 86.08 - internal release only.
2010-05-16: Rename getline() to jlss_getline() to avoid conflict with POSIX
            2008 version of getline(), found in <stdio.h> in recent Linux.
2010-05-16: Configure now uses ./program to test ESQL/C for dot-less PATH.

Version 86.07
-------------
2010-04-11: Version 86.07 - internal release only.
2010-04-11: Redo ifx_var_dealloc() fix - GCC 3.4.5 on Linux not happy.

Version 86.06
-------------
2010-04-11: Version 86.06 - internal release only.
2010-04-11: Fix argument handling (remove -G, -W support; do not list -n).
2010-01-06: Richard Fahey <RFahey@west.com> reported a core dump in
            sqlupload.  Reproduces on MacOS X - crash was in
            ifx_var_dealloc() in describe.ec.  The problem can be seen
            when looking at the ifx_var_flag() code, and then comparing
            it with the ifx_var_dealloc().

