Version 86.01
-------------
2008-12-31: Version 86.01 - never formally released.
2008-11-03: Edit sqlcmd.1 to clarify support for basic IUS types (BOOLEAN,
            LVARCHAR, INT8, BIGINT, SERIAL8, BIGSERIAL) prompted by a question
            from Joe R Plugge <JRPlugge@west.com>.
2008-10-21: Fix connecty.y so it can work as a test program (again).
2008-09-19: AutoConf 2.63 marks AC_TYPE_SIGNAL as obsolescent (can safely
            assume RETSIGTYPE is void everywhere).  Remove use of both
            macro and type.
2008-08-17: SQLCMD: Detect program name better (sqlreload.64 == sqlreload).
2008-08-15: Configure now checks that ESQL/C compiler 'works'.
2008-08-01: Update version information - per "Software Craftsmanship" by
            Pete McBreen.

Version 86.00
-------------
2008-07-15: Version 86.00 - released to IIUG Software Archive.
2008-07-15: SQLCMD: Include test suite now that it has been upgraded to be
            manageable; run with 'make test'.  Include a SCHEDULE file from
            1992, just for curiosity - shows what testing should be in
            place but isn't.
2008-07-13: SQLCMD: describe.ec v2007.1 (2007-02-10) broke loading of
            LVARCHAR, so afflicts 81.00 onwards.  Workaround coded, but
            long-term solution probably involves rather dramatic changes.
2008-07-12: SQLCMD: revise code to recognize dbase@server:owner.table
            in LOAD statements, including DELIMIDENT support.  Also minor
            fix ups in test suite.

