Version 78.00
-------------
2005-05-06: Version 78.00 uploaded to IIUG.
2005-05-06: SQLCMD: Add support for 'fixsep' format - fixed format output
            with field separators (current field delimiter).
2005-05-06: SQLCMD: The '@' prefix to commands is officially deprecated,
            and support will be removed after 2006-06-30.
2005-05-06: SQLCMD: Try to permit unquoted file names in LOAD, UNLOAD and
            RELOAD.  It is not readily doable - this deviation from the
            Informix tools is now formally documented.
2005-05-03: SQLCMD: Add 'help' built-in command.  Need to sort out I18N.
2005-04-29: SQLCMD: Add '-X record=rectag,recset=settag,header=hdrtag'
            support, using getsubopt().  Deprecate '-G rectag' - it still
            works but is redundant; support for it will be dropped after
            2006-06-30.  Revise 'format xml' to accept the new notation.

Version 77.08
-------------
2005-04-22: Version 77.08 uploaded to IIUG.
2005-04-22: SQLCMD: Fix XML output heading - bug reported by Roy Mercer
            <roy.mercer@gmail.com>.  Output now accepted by Firefox 1.0.3
            as XML, albeit without any style information.  Remove the
            dubious encoding information.  Convert the heading XML tags to
            lower case.

Version 77.07
-------------
2005-04-01: Version 77.07 uploaded to IIUG.
2005-04-01: LIBRARY: make sure tokencmp.h has size_t so it compiles on
            HP-UX; found by Randy Kennedy <rkennedy@scottsdaleaz.gov>.
2005-04-01: SQLCMD: Change of mind; -N 0 will not be supported.  Use a
            number bigger than the number of rows in your data file.  Do
            not try to load more than 2 billion rows in a single TX.

Version 77.06
-------------
2005-03-31: Version 77.06 on limited release.
2005-03-31: SQLCMD: CSV output follows Excel and uses doubled up quotes
            rather than backslash quote.  Document -G in extended help.
            Fix the counting during RELOAD.
2005-03-30: SQLCMD: Support SKIP n in LOAD and RELOAD (-S n on command
            line).  Permit -N 0 to suppress sub-transactions in RELOAD.

Version 77.05
-------------
2005-03-25: Version 77.05 released to IIUG.
2005-03-25: SQLCMD: Fix loading problems with CSV data containing commas
            or quotes in strings, after a question raised by
            <try_and_err@web.de> in comp.databases.informix on
            2005-03-17.  Rework the internals of readload.c with
            separate CSV field scanning logic - based on the code from
            Kernighan & Pike 'The Practice of Programming' (see
            http://tpop.awl.com/).

Version 77.04
-------------
2005-03-18: Version 77.04 released.
2005-03-18: SQLCMD: Fix problems reading commands with backslashes in
            strings.  Fix problems reading load files where the last
            character of the last field is a backslash.

